257
00:16:22,950 --> 00:16:25,455
Then he wasn't a witch.
But at least we know then.

258
00:16:25,572 --> 00:16:27,396
How are you so sure about that?

259
00:16:27,874 --> 00:16:29,199
I learned that today...

260
00:16:29,510 --> 00:16:30,829
in history class.

261
00:16:32,827 --> 00:16:33,990
What are you doing?

262
00:16:34,040 --> 00:16:35,985
Just look at how proud Ms. Glee is.

263
00:16:37,801 --> 00:16:40,112
Shame. I was looking
forward to the fireworks.

264
00:16:40,853 --> 00:16:43,939
Drown him, drown him, drown him!

265
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,120
Drown him, drown him!

266
00:16:45,248 --> 00:16:47,288
Drown him, drown him, drown him!

267
00:16:47,330 --> 00:16:50,430
Drown him, drown him, drown him!

268
00:16:50,431 --> 00:16:54,811
Drown him, drown him, drown him!

269
00:16:54,832 --> 00:16:55,804
Drown him!

270
00:16:59,408 --> 00:17:02,125
To the fireplace in
the teachers' lounge.

271
00:17:49,890 --> 00:17:51,729
Witch, witch, witch!

272
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:54,080
Witch, witch, witch!

273
00:17:54,172 --> 00:17:56,050
Witch, witch, witch!

274
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:58,000
Witch, witch, witch!

275
00:17:58,050 --> 00:17:59,760
Witch, witch, witch!

276
00:17:59,761 --> 00:18:02,892
Guys, guys. Listen to me for a second.

277
00:18:02,940 --> 00:18:05,259
Guys, please listen to me for a bit.

278
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:08,503
Take Barteljaap out of
the water immediately.

279
00:18:08,797 --> 00:18:11,777
Oh, wait a second. I just
want to explain why.

280
00:18:12,221 --> 00:18:13,980
I just have to catch my breath.

281
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:16,960
What was it I wanted to say again?
Oh, right.

282
00:18:17,172 --> 00:18:19,890
Speaking as vice-principal
of this school...

283
00:18:19,909 --> 00:18:22,869
and also as a human,
too, actually, somewhat...

284
00:18:23,149 --> 00:18:27,295
I just wanted to say... You in
the water, can you quiet down?

285
00:18:27,389 --> 00:18:30,167
Can you please be quiet?
I'm trying to hold a speech.

286
00:18:30,930 --> 00:18:32,202
Just a few words.

287
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:35,395
Guys, I learned something today.

288
00:18:35,880 --> 00:18:40,624
I learned that things in a book...

289
00:18:40,735 --> 00:18:42,352
aren't always true.

290
00:18:42,664 --> 00:18:44,930
And that you shouldn't believe...

291
00:18:44,980 --> 00:18:48,695
the things that a stranger
writes down in a book.

292
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:52,930
And also that the toilet should
really only be used for dumps.

293
00:18:53,159 --> 00:18:56,281
Oh, and one more important thing.

294
00:18:57,495 --> 00:19:01,298
Can I interest someone to
adopt my owl? It's a white owl.

295
00:19:02,173 --> 00:19:04,488
50 euros. Hardly used. Nobody?

296
00:19:04,535 --> 00:19:06,721
No one at all? Oh, well.

297
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:10,400
Alright then.
- Help, help!

298
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:13,715
What are you waiting for? Get
that man out of the water!

299
00:19:23,334 --> 00:19:27,040
So, boys and girls. What
Mr. Hulst is trying to say is...

300
00:19:27,835 --> 00:19:29,910
that this is crearly nonesense.

301
00:19:30,311 --> 00:19:32,431
Sometimes things seem
to be supernatural...

302
00:19:32,436 --> 00:19:34,720
but there is always a
logical explanation for it.

303
00:19:34,721 --> 00:19:37,903
Witchcraft, sorcery:
it doesn't exist.

304
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:40,480
Just like how gnomes don't exist, and...

305
00:19:40,511 --> 00:19:43,374
sorry to break it to you,
sister Innocentia,

306
00:19:43,407 --> 00:19:45,875
God doesn't exist either.

307
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:50,395
Hey, ouch! Goddamnit!

308
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:58,970
Blasphemer! Heretic!

309
00:19:59,020 --> 00:20:01,232
This is your punishment!

310
00:20:01,302 --> 00:20:06,847
Don't you see that He is truly
everywhere, everytime?

311
00:20:07,284 --> 00:20:09,009
And I'm talking about God!

312
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,192
God, the one and only!

313
00:20:12,731 --> 00:20:15,950
And not about that mad Hindu!

314
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:18,710
Not that fatty of a Buddha!

315
00:20:18,980 --> 00:20:22,365
Not Krishna, not Jahweh...

316
00:20:22,622 --> 00:20:27,240
not Thor and definitely not about...

317
00:20:30,454 --> 00:20:32,854
God, get me! Please, take me!

318
00:20:36,930 --> 00:20:39,655
Look at that. Ms. Glee is back.

319
00:20:42,119 --> 00:20:43,424
She's all back to normal.

320
00:20:43,557 --> 00:20:45,950
Please, get me too!

321
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,120
Please!

322
00:20:48,220 --> 00:20:50,054
I hate you all!

323
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:53,378
She's back to normal.

324
00:20:53,917 --> 00:20:54,895
Release me!

325
00:20:57,398 --> 00:20:59,683
All because of my kiss,
after all. I knew it.

326
00:20:59,770 --> 00:21:00,603
No way.

327
00:21:00,829 --> 00:21:03,969
She has been so touched because
she taught me something...

328
00:21:04,252 --> 00:21:06,015
That she doesn't feel down anymore.

329
00:21:07,603 --> 00:21:09,148
I'm such a special boy.

